RM  9882686
RT  Isolation and characterization of the nikR gene encoding a
RT  nickel-responsive regulator in Escherichia coli.
RA  De Pina K, Desjardin V, Mandrand-Berthelot MA, Giordano G, Wu LF;
RL  J Bacteriol. 1999;181:670-674.
CC  Nickel is an essential trace element, but is also toxic at high levels. 
CC  This genome property descibes a specifc ABC transporter that is responsible 
CC  for the uptake of nickel. The transporter is encoded by the nikABCDE operon.
CC  This property also includes nikR which has been shown to function as a 
CC  regulator for this transporter [1,2,3].
